Evaluate probability of response

Females responded in 30 out of 39 total trials (77% of trials). Males responded together with the female in 27 of these trials (90% of responsive trials) and we only analyzed responses witha female response. In total, we completed 17 presentations in the ornamented female population (M.a.moretoni) and 13 presentations in the unornamented female population (M.a.lorentzi). Neither subspecies (glm females: z=0.004,p=0.997; glm males: z=0,p=1) or song (glm females: z=0.006, p=0.995; glm males: z=-0.006, p=0.995) predicted the likelihood of response.
